data.title: The world's royals appear in a newly released group photo taken at the wedding of Jordan's Crown Prince Hussein and Saudi architect Princess Rajwa: The best photos
data.meta_description: See all the best photos from the royal wedding of Jordan's Crown Prince Hussein and his new bride, Princess Rajwa.
data.text:
_

In August 2022, Jordan's future king, Crown Prince Hussein — the eldest son of King Abdullah II and Queen Rania — announced his engagement to Rajwa Al Saif, a Saudi national who attended the College of Architecture at Syracuse University in New York. Nine months later, the couple wed in front of European, Asian and Middle Eastern royals including Britain's Prince William and Princess Kate, the king and queen of The Netherlands, crown princes and princesses of other European nations, the Sultan of Brunei and other notable guests including America's first lady, Jill Biden. Keep reading to see the best photos from the Jordanian prince's beautiful nuptials…

Kings, queens, princes and princesses from royal families across the globe — including Britain's Princess Kate and Prince William (top row just right of center) — posed with Jordan's royal family including newlyweds Crown Prince Hussein and Princess Rajwa before the couple's wedding banquet at Al Husseiniya Palace in Amman, Jordan, on June 1, 2023.

MORE: Follow Wonderwall on MSN for more fun celebrity & entertainment photo galleries and content

Following their wedding ceremony, Jordan's Crown Prince Hussein and his bride, Princess Rajwa — who wore a custom gown by Elie Saab with white flats — arrive at Al Husseiniya Palace in Amman, Jordan, on June 1, 2023, to celebrate with a banquet dinner and concert.
